---
import Counter from "../components/Counter.astro";
import DeferredWrapper from "../components/DeferredWrapper.astro";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <title>Server Island Script Bug</title>
    <style>
      body { font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; max-width: 800px; margin: 2rem auto; }
      .test { margin: 2rem 0; padding: 1rem; background: #f5f5f5; border-radius: 8px; }
      h2 { margin-top: 0; }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>Server Island Script Bug — Minimal Reproduction</h1>

    <div class="test">
      <h2>✅ Control: Counter rendered directly on the page</h2>
      <p>This button works because the script is included in the page.</p>
      <Counter />
    </div>

    <div class="test">
      <h2>🐛 Bug: Counter passed as slot to server:defer component</h2>
      <p>This button does NOT work. The Counter HTML renders but its <code>&lt;script&gt;</code> is silently dropped.</p>
      <p>Note: the control Counter's script doesn't help here either — it already ran <em>before</em> the island response injected this Counter into the DOM.</p>
      <DeferredWrapper server:defer>
        <div slot="fallback">⏳ Loading server island...</div>
        <Counter slot="content" />
      </DeferredWrapper>
    </div>

    <div class="test">
      <h2>How to verify</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Open DevTools → Console. You should see <code>✅ Counter script executed</code> only <strong>once</strong> (from the control), not twice.</li>
        <li>Click "Increment" on the first counter — it works.</li>
        <li>Click "Increment" on the second counter — nothing happens.</li>
        <li>Open DevTools → Network: inspect the <code>/_server-islands/</code> response — it contains the Counter HTML but zero <code>&lt;script&gt;</code> tags.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
